1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,339
My fellow Americans.
2
00:00:02,339 --> 00:00:08,220
This day has brought terrible news, and great sadness to our country.
3
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:11,640
At nine o'clock this morning.
4
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:16,679
Mission Control in Houston, lost contact with our space shuttle, Columbia.
5
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:23,160
A short time later, debris was seen falling from the skies above Texas.
6
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:25,800
The Columbia's lost.
7
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:28,379
There are no survivors.
8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,559
On board was a crew of seven.
9
00:00:31,620 --> 00:00:34,619
Colonel Rick husband,
10
00:00:34,619 --> 00:00:48,960
Lieutenant Colonel Michael Anderson, Commander Laurel Clark, Captain David Brown, Commander William McCool, Dr. Coultna Chauvelin, and Elon Ramon, a
11
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,240
Colonel in the Israeli Air Force.
12
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:56,880
These men and women assumed great risk in the service to all humanity.
13
00:00:57,420 --> 00:01:01,859
In an age when space flight has come to seem almost routine.
14
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:10,319
It is easy to overlook the dangers of travel by rocket, and the difficulties of navigating the fierce outer atmosphere of the
15
00:01:10,319 --> 00:01:10,620
earth.
16
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:16,920
These astronauts knew the dangers, and they faced them willingly.
17
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:21,000
Knowing they had a high and noble purpose in life.
18
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:26,280
Because of their courage and daring and idealism.
19
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:28,799
We will miss them all the more.
20
00:01:29,579 --> 00:01:35,280
All Americans to day, are thinking as well, of the families of these men and women.
21
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:38,819
Who have been given this sudden shock and grief.
22
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:41,040
You're not alone.
23
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:43,980
Our entire nation grieves with you.
24
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:49,920
And those you loved will always have the respect and gratitude of this
25
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:50,400
country.
26
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:55,079
The cause in which they died will continue.
27
00:01:55,500 --> 00:02:02,159
Mankind is led into the darkness, beyond our world, by the inspiration of
28
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:05,280
discovery, and the longing to understand.
29
00:02:05,939 --> 00:02:09,840
Our journey into space will go on.
30
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:15,180
In the skies to day, we saw destruction and tragedy.
31
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:18,360
Yet farther than we can see.
32
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,580
There is comfort and hope.
33
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:30,300
In the words of the prophet Isaiah, Lift your eyes, and look to the heavens, who created all these,
34
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:34,319
he who brings out the starry hosts one by one,
35
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:37,560
and calls them, each by name,
36
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:42,360
because of his great power, and mighty strength.
37
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,759
Not one of them is missing.
38
00:02:45,419 --> 00:02:51,960
The same creator who names the stars, also knows the names of
39
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,180
the seven souls we mourn to day.
40
00:02:54,419 --> 00:02:59,639
The crew of the shuttle Columbia did not return safely to earth.
41
00:02:59,759 --> 00:03:04,199
Yet we can pray that all are safely home.
42
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:09,960
May God bless the grieving families, and may God, may
43
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,719
God continue to bless, America.
